WHAT'S CHANGEDFortescue Metals Group Ltd. (FMG.AX)FromToPrice TargetA$19.40A$19.90Bull CaseA$36.05A$34.80Base CaseA$17.35A$16.35Bear CaseA$8.90A$9.20Updated ComponentsEPS
Risk Reward for Fortescue Metals Group Ltd. (FMG.AX) has been updated

We update our model for the FY25 result, which sees our EPS to fall \(5.4\%\) to US \(1.10 / \mathrm{sh}\) . We also update our costs and capex estimates, which sees our FY26e and FY27e EPS to rise \(3.8\% /4.3\%\) to US \(1.09 / \mathrm{sh}\) and US \(1.03 / \mathrm{sh}\) respectively.

In all, our base case valuation by falls by \(A\$ 1 / \mathrm{sh}\) , to \(A\$ 16.35 / \mathrm{sh}\) . Our bull case valuation falls \(A\$ 1.25 / \mathrm{sh}\) to \(A\$ 34.80 / \mathrm{sh}\) , and our bear case valuation rises 30cps, to \(A\$ 9.20 / \mathrm{sh}\) , as we update our debt and working capital assumptions. We increase our bull weight, with our bull/base/bear weights now \(25\% /60\% /15\%\) (prev. \(20\% /60\% /20\%\) ) due to improved spot cash flows on FX and Iron ore prices and above our base case.
Overall, our price target rises 50cps, to \(A\$ 19.90 / \mathrm{sh}\) .
MORGAN STANLEY AUSTRALIA LIMITED+

Upside limited, but attractive yield
Key: Historical Stock Performance Current Stock Price Price Target

We view any potential near- term iron ore weakness as fairly priced in heading into FY26. FMG continues its strong cash generation, and ramp- up at Iron Bridge should improve group average iron ore grades. Risks surrounding decarbonisation spending remain, and lead us to forecast lower FCF yields in FY25- 26 vs. recent years. However, we see this as priced in with opportunity to the upside. Although upside to our increased price target is limited, attractive dividend yield keeps us at OW.
